[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A clinical trial recruitment conversationalist decomposes into ten logical stages: trial-portfolio ingestion with IRB-material lifecycle, eligibility-criteria modeling, optional cohort-matching against EHR data with research-purpose-of-use governance, channel entry with consent-aware authentication, input safety screening with continuous emergency screening, identity-and-context loading, conversation handling with IRB-material-grounded responses, output safety screening with persuasive-pattern verification, expression-of-interest capture with coordinator handoff, and audit and reporting with sponsor-IRB-site contracted boundaries. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.9 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (IRB-approved material as system of record for participant-facing content, eligibility-criteria-as-structured-predicates with deterministic logic, cohort-matching as separately-governed subsystem, consent-process boundary enforcement, and equity-in-trials monitoring as launch-gate discipline).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── TRIAL PORTFOLIO + IRB MATERIAL LIFECYCLE ──────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Trial registry]                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-trial entry with sponsor, NCT identifier,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      protocol identifier, IRB approval status,            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      recruitment status (active, paused, closed),         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      enrollment target, current enrollment, schedule of   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      assessments, study locations, PI per site,           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      coordinator-of-record per site                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-trial protocol-content with version              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-trial recruitment material with IRB-approved     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      version stamps (recruitment page, plain-language     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      summary, FAQ content, consent-form-content for       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      education purposes, schedule-of-assessments          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      summary, multi-language translations)                │
