[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the recruitment conversationalist.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IRB-approved-material as system of record for participant-facing content.** Every recruitment message, plain-language description, FAQ answer, and consent-education content has an IRB-approved source with a recorded version stamp. The conversationalist does not produce participant-facing content outside this lineage. The version stamps flow through the conversation log, the recruitment-decision-record journal, and the audit pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Eligibility-criteria-as-structured-predicates with deterministic logic.** Each criterion has a structured predicate, version-controlled, signed off by clinical-research leadership and the IRB. The LLM presents the criterion conversationally and handles patient questions; the LLM does not evaluate the criterion. The deterministic engine evaluates the criterion against patient-reported and (where consented) chart-derived data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Trial-corpus registry with real-time-or-near-real-time status tracking.** The trial portfolio is a curated registry, not the LLM's training data. Active/paused/closed status, IRB-approval status, recruitment-material version, and eligibility-criteria-model version are tracked centrally and consumed by the conversationalist.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cohort-matching as separately-governed subsystem.** Cohort matching against EHR data operates under explicit research-purpose-of-use governance per HIPAA pathway, IRB approval per cohort-matching activity, audit trails per matching pass, and per-cohort equity safeguards. The matching results inform outreach and surface likely-eligible trials during conversation; the matching itself is not the LLM.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Consent-process boundary enforcement.** The conversationalist supports consent-process education and Q&A; the conversationalist does not collect, witness, or confirm informed consent. The boundary is enforced architecturally (consent-collect tool does not exist in the conversationalist's surface) and verified in the output safety stage.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Persuasive-pattern avoidance as architectural primitive.** The system prompt forbids it, the output safety detects it, the sampled review tags it as a failure mode, the conversation review process specifically watches for it. The IRB's role in approving recruitment material is reinforced by the architectural discipline of refusing to produce content the IRB has not approved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Equity-in-trials monitoring with launch-gate discipline.** Per-cohort outreach reach, engagement, pre-screen, expression-of-interest, screen-show, and enrollment metrics are reviewed by clinical-research leadership, IRB, equity leadership, and patient-advocacy. Launch-gate thresholds for per-cohort metrics are established before deployment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Coordinator-handoff pathway as production scope.** The handoff is a first-class workflow with structured pre-screening data, conversation excerpts with citations, IRB-approved-material version stamps, coordinator-availability awareness, and follow-up scheduling. The handoff format is co-designed with coordinator workforce leadership.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Sponsor-IRB-site contracted boundaries.** In multi-site or sponsor-funded deployments, the data-flow respects contracted boundaries. The architecture enforces the boundaries; the LLM does not.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    766[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    767[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous emergency screening across every utterance.** Same as the previous bots in this chapter. The conversationalist routes acute emergencies, mental-health crises, and clinically-significant events appropriately; the conversationalist does not try to handle them in scope.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    768[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    769[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every recruitment message cites its IRB-approved-material source with version. Every eligibility-criterion explanation cites its criteria-model entry. Every FAQ answer cites its FAQ entry. Every consent-form education delivery cites its consent-form content with version. Citations are structured and the audit record preserves the citation trail.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    770[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    771[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IRB-material lifecycle integration.** The IRB-material lifecycle (drafted, IRB-reviewed, IRB-approved, in use, amended, re-IRB-approved, retired) is an operational pipeline. The conversationalist consumes the in-use versions. Amendments propagate via a controlled release process with sign-off records.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    772[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    773[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Recruitment metrics, engagement metrics, conversion metrics, and outcome metrics vary by language, channel, condition, age cohort, sex, race, ethnicity, socioeconomic context, geography, and trial-portfolio segment. Per-cohort dashboards are reviewed by clinical-research leadership, IRB, equity leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    774[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    775[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the trial-corpus registry, the IRB-material content store, the eligibility-criteria-model store, the cohort-matching subsystem, the coordinator-handoff queue, or any escalation pathway is unreachable, the conversationalist degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble pulling that information right now; for trial-related questions please contact the research coordinator at [number]." The graceful-degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    776[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    777[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    778[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
